Upon further cycling, a stable value is reached at around 275 mV (Supplementary Fig. 16). By studying Tafel slopes (Fig. 5b) one can gain some insight into the improved electrocatalysis of the optimized electrode. Graphs of this kind are based on the Tafel equation (Eq. (2)), which relates the overpotential η to the current density j (and exchange current density j0) so that the proportionality constant b (Tafel slope) will give information regarding the sensitivity of the reaction rate to a change in potential across the cell:1η=b×log10jj0\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
